  "title": "Farmer participatory varietal selection in groundnut – A success story in Anantapur, Andhra Pradesh, India",
  "abstract": "Farmer participatory varietal selection trials in Anantapur, Andhra Pradesh, India identified ICGV 91114 as the most productive groundnut cultivar. This cultivar was adopted for large-scale production, giving higher pod and haulm yields and comparable shelling outturn compared with the control cultivar TMV 2.",
